		<div class="right_content left">
			<div class="inner_page_title">
				Waseda University			</div>			
			<div class="summer_image"><img   src='/files/programs-waseda-img01.jpg' alt="" /></div>
<div class="clearfix container">
<div class="left content">
<div class="paragraph">Founded in 1882 by Shigenobu Okuma, once prime minister and regarded as the father of Japanese national modernization, Waseda has since grown from a college with 3 departments to a comprehensive university.</div>
<table class="table_styling">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Students</td>
<td>54,000 including 4,700 international</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Bai Xian Asian Scholars<br />(from 2014)</td>
<td>15</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style="border-right: 1px solid #efefef;" colspan="2"><em>Scholarship places are offered for admission to the School of Political Science and Economics only</em></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<div class="list">
<div class="list-title">Unique Program Offerings</div>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>Undergraduate "double degrees" with top universities in Asia, including Peking University, Fudan University and National Taiwan University</li>
<li>Students tailor their own study plans with a focus on either political science or economics&nbsp;</li>
<li>Equip students with skills and knowledge to propose new strategies and solutions for resolving global and Asian issues</li>
<li>Bai Xian Asian Scholars will team up with local Japanese students to work together on projects, study tours, and summer camps</li>
<li>Internship opportunities may be available at some of Japan&rsquo;s most prestigious companies</li>
</ul>
</ul>
<br /><br />
<ul>
<ul>
<ul>
<ul>
<ul>
<ul>* Waseda University operates an independent selection process for the Asian Future Leaders Scholarship Program. Please apply for admission and contact the university directly to express your interest.</ul>
</ul>
</ul>
</ul>
</ul>
</ul>
</div>
